\f3\fs20 Good evening. Here\'92s the latest.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 1. At least 20 Americans are among those who have been infected with the new coronavirus on a cruise ship quarantined in a Japanese port.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 More than 2,500 passengers on board are being kept in effective isolation, eating meals in their cabins and keeping at least six feet from each other during the few minutes each day they are allowed on deck. And the situation is worse for crew members, who live elbow to elbow in cramped quarters.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 China had extended its official Lunar New Year holiday by 10 days to help counter the virus\'92s spread. But when the extension ended today, stores and factories remained empty, suggesting it could be weeks \'97 or months \'97 before one of the world\'92s largest economies is humming again. Above, President Xi Jinping, who has remained conspicuously absent in recent weeks, made a       \'a0    rare public appearance to address the crisis.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 In our Opinion section, an epidemiologist who is heading to the World Health Organization\'92s emergency meeting on Tuesday lists what is known, and not yet known, about the virus.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 2. New Hampshire is next.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 The state\'92s Democratic presidential primary, the second contest in the 2020 race, is on Tuesday. Bernie Sanders, above, is leading in the polls, and Pete Buttigieg isn\'92t far behind.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 The two are trying to capitalize on their strong showings in the troubled Iowa caucuses, while increasingly training their fire on each other. Elizabeth Warren is       \'a0    reviving her rallying cry (\'93Still, she persisted\'94), the political outsider Andrew Yang faces a       \'a0    make-or-break moment, and Joe Biden is already looking beyond to       \'a0    his \'93firewall\'94 in South Carolina.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 Here are our live updates as candidates dash around New Hampshire.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 Iowa: The problems with the caucuses were bigger than one bad app. According to an investigation by our reporters, there was a total system failure.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 3. President Trump released a $4.8 trillion budget proposal, but it has little chance of being fully enacted by Congress.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 As is usual, it\'92s more of a messaging document. The message: Keep shrinking the federal safety net, with deep cuts to student loan assistance, affordable housing, food stamps and Medicaid, and slash the E.P.A. Add funds to the military, national defense and border enforcement.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 Mr. Trump faces a secure spot in New Hampshire\'92s Republican primary, with just one opponent: Bill Weld, the former Massachusetts governor.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 We\'92ll be in Manchester, N.H., for Mr. Trump\'92s rally tonight.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 4. Four members of China\'92s military were charged in the vast 2017 Equifax data breach, which exposed the personal information of about 145 million Americans.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 The U.S. government said the attack was part of a series of big data thefts organized by the People\'92s Liberation Army and Chinese intelligence agencies. Hackers stole names, birth dates and Social Security numbers of nearly half of all Americans \'97 data that could be combined with artificial intelligence to help identify and target U.S. intelligence officers.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 And in Israel, a \'93grave\'94 security lapse in an election app promoted by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu led to the exposure of personal data of all 6.5 million eligible voters.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 5. Angela Merkel\'92s chosen successor to lead Germany has stepped aside.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 Annegret Kramp-Karrenbauer, above, announced her resignation after a local chapter of her party, the center-right Christian Democrats, allied itself with a rising far-right party, Alternative for Germany.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 At a time when neighboring countries are looking to Berlin for leadership in a post-Brexit Europe, Germany is struggling with an uncomfortable sense of having lived through this before, as the growing power of the far right echoes the rise of the Nazis.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 6. New rules at U.S. schools and colleges will shore up protections for victims of stalking and dating violence.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 The rules will for the first time cement domestic violence, dating violence and stalking as forms of gender discrimination that schools must address. Victims\'92 rights advocates say that while many schools have presumed such infractions fall under the broad umbrella of sexual harassment, not all have trained their staffs to address them.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 Above, a memorial to Lauren McCluskey, a University of Utah track star who was kidnapped on campus and killed by a former boyfriend in 2018, and whose case helped inspire the changes.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 7. The Dart Container Corporation was an American success story. But it built its fortune on a modern environmental pariah: foam containers.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 As states like New York, Maine and Maryland outlaw polystyrene foam, which can harm fish and other marine life, the company that helped spur a revolution in cups and clamshells is struggling to find a path forward.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 And in Africa, researchers found that an increase in temperatures over the past seven decades correlates with bigger and more frequent thunderstorms. That increase, combined with poor infrastructure, could mean more fatalities and more economic damage.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 8. California was about to lose its oldest weekly newspaper. And then in stepped Carl Butz.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 Since his retirement and his wife\'92s death in 2017, Mr. Butz had considered traveling to England or Latvia, or riding the Trans-Siberian Railway. But one night, he said, he was watching \'93Citizen Kane\'94 on cable and thought, I can do that.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 So the 71-year-old cut a four-figure deal to buy The Mountain Messenger, earning himself a new career and saving Downieville, Calif., from becoming the latest small town to lose its newspaper.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 9. Lessons from the \'93Parasite\'94 landslide.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 The South Korean film\'92s triumph as the first non-English language best picture winner is a result in part of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences\'92 efforts to diversify its voting base by race, gender, and nationality. It has added hundreds of new members from outside the U.S.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 \'93The success of \'91Parasite\'92 makes me wonder if the best picture win for a middlebrow nothing like \'91Green Book\'92 last year was more anomalous than it seemed,\'94 said Manohla Dargis, in a conversation with fellow Times critics A.O. Scott and Wesley Morris.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 From the Oscars red carpet, our chief fashion critic, Vanessa Friedman, writes that \'93Janelle Mon\'e1e, in silver crystal-covered, hooded Ralph Lauren, had the best dress. She looked like the ruler of an entire galaxy.\'94 
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 But the fashionista firepower wasn\'92t enough for TV viewers: The audience fell 20 percent, to an all-time low of 23.6 million.
\f0\fs24 \

\f3\fs20 10. What\'92s better than a bichon fris\'e9? Four bichons fris\'e9s.
