It was a busy week in the Democratic presidential campaign, with a flood of new policies and, of course, another debate.\
Let\'92s get right to it.\
A surprisingly subdued debate\
There weren\'92t a lot of sparks in this week\'92s debate, the fifth of the Democratic primary. But in the absence of a clear front-runner, several lower-polling candidates were able to break through \'97 at least for one news cycle.\
Senators Kamala Harris of California, Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota and Cory Booker of New Jersey all had strong nights. So did Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., who did not face nearly as many attacks as expected in his first appearance since he shot to the top of the field in Iowa.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls19\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	Alexander Burns and Jonathan Martin have the full recap.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls20\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	Here are five takeaways, and a look at       \'a0    the biggest moments of the night.\
