\ls23\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	Reid J. Epstein wrote about how badly Mr. Buttigieg is struggling with black voters.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl260\sb200\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The candidates courted black voters\
After the debate, several candidates fanned across Atlanta to pitch themselves to black audiences.\
Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts gave a speech at Clark Atlanta University on Thursday evening, saying that \'93race-neutral laws\'94 were not enough, and that the government had an obligation to mend the damage caused by \'93decades of active, state-sponsored discrimination.\'94 She was joined onstage by Representative Ayanna Pressley of Massachusetts, who has endorsed her, and Ms. Pressley ended up speaking directly to pro-charter-school protesters who interrupted the speech.\
Earlier in the day, Ms. Harris held a \'93black women\'92s breakfast,\'94 and Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont gave a speech tying his family\'92s experience in the Holocaust to the discrimination black Americans face.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls24\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	You can read more about Ms. Warren\'92s rally here.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls25\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	Michael R. Bloomberg, who has long defended his mayoral administration\'92s stop-and-frisk policy in New York, apologized for it this week as he continues to move toward a presidential campaign. The policy disproportionately affected people of color.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl260\sb200\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Messam is out\
Mayor Wayne Messam of Miramar, Fla., ended his presidential campaign on Wednesday. \
If you hadn\'92t known he was running to begin with, well, don\'92t worry about it. Mr. Messam had never appeared on a debate stage, reaching only 1 percent in exactly two debate-qualifying polls all year, and had raised a mere $15,000 in the third quarter.\
\'93I knew the odds were a steep hill to climb, but I have always fought for what is right and will continue to break barriers never broken,\'94 he said in announcing his withdrawal.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls26\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	You can read more about Mr. Messam here.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl260\sb200\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Policies from \'85 well, everyone\
Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. introduced a wide-ranging plan this week to expand on the Violence Against Women Act.\
Among other things, it would create a new housing program for survivors of sexual assault and domestic abuse, require colleges and universities to improve reporting systems, establish a task force on online harassment and provide $100 million a year to end the backlog of untested rape kits.\
The proposal also focuses on survivors\'92 ability to sue: It would ban mandatory arbitration clauses that block employees from suing over sexual harassment and restore a provision in the act that would allow people to take civil action against their abusers in federal court. The Supreme Court blocked that provision in 1999, and Mr. Biden is calling on Congress to pass a version that \'93fills the gaps the Court found fatal last time.\'94\
In other policy news:\
Mr. Biden was one of seven candidates who released plans this week \'97 including Ms. Warren, who, as is her wont, released two.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls27\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	In a plan to combat white nationalism, Ms. Warren pledged to make prosecuting domestic terrorism a top Justice Department and Homeland Security priority, require local and state governments to report suspected hate crimes and create a federal task force to combat radicalization. The plan also includes gun control and police reform proposals.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls28\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	Ms. Warren\'92s other new plan, on \'93protecting and empowering renters,\'94 is an extension of her previous housing proposal. It calls for more protections against eviction, funding for local efforts to provide legal representation for tenants who cannot afford it, a federal hotline for tenant complaints and new public housing.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls29\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	Mr. Buttigieg released his alternative to \'93free college for all\'94 plans. It would make public colleges free for families earning up to $100,000 a year, subsidize tuition for those earning up to $150,000 and increase Pell Grant funding by $120 billion. He also addresses student loan repayment, apprenticeships and food security for students.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls30\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	Mr. Sanders also addressed education in his latest plan, which focuses on historically black colleges and universities. He wants to make tuition free at all H.B.C.U.s, both public and private; let low-income students use Pell Grants for books and living expenses; and expand training programs at H.B.C.U.s for public schoolteachers.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls31\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	Andrew Yang, in a new voting rights plan, proposed banning voter ID requirements, regulating voter roll purges more strictly and allowing same-day registration and more early and absentee voting. His plan also addresses obstacles for Native Americans and people with disabilities, and calls for lowering the voting age to 16 and allowing people in prison to vote.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls32\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	Tom Steyer announced a health care plan based on a public option. It would be separate from Medicare and Medicaid but administered by the same agency, and medical providers who accept Medicare and Medicaid would be required to accept the public option as well.\
\pard\tx760\pardeftab720\li760\fi-400\ri0\sl260\sb120\qj\partightenfactor0
\ls33\ilvl0\cf0 \'95	Gov. Steve Bullock of Montana released a mental health plan that would increase funding for mental health care providers, make Medicaid cover inpatient treatment and end solitary confinement for people with serious mental illnesses, among other measures.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl260\sb200\qj\partightenfactor0
